race.comment: PONDALOWIE (7) is an interesting one in the Cup. She's been plagued by a few bad barriers this time in, getting a mile back in a G3 race at Caulfield last time out but finding the line well in a slowly run race. The run two back was also very good and if she can land midfield here she'll go close. COTE ATLANTIQUE (1) beat EL ROCKO (2)  in the Seymour Cup last time out. EL ROCKO meets COTE ATLANTIQUE 2.5kg worse off at the weights for that narrow defeat but arguably has a bit more upside and can go on with it. CARTOON GRAVEYARD (6) was a strong winner of the Murray Bridge Cup when last seen, running strong overall time. He stays down in the weights here and looks a danger. SCHEELITE (8) did enough fresh at Caulfield and drops 6kg off that.
